as part of the settlement indian river power will investigate and evaluate the opacity violations on units  and  implement an optimization plan for the electrostatic precipitators particulate control devices for units    and  and establish policies to minimize opacity and nitrogen oxides violations the settlement will also require indian river power to purchase and provide to the department an ultrafine particle monitor and pay a civil penalty of  in  dnrec and nrg signed a consent decree requiring the facility to dramatically cut air pollutants by  dnrec issued a permit for the construction of the phase ii industrial landfill in october  construction of cell  of the phase ii landfill was completed in september  and that cell is currently in use dnrec has also issued acid rain and title v permits to the indian river power plant permits in addition dnrecs site investigation and restoration section has issued a final plan of remedial action for operable units    for the adjacent burton island ash disposal area please see secretarys order no a – approval of final plan of remedial action for burton island ash disposal area operable units    in millsboro  the proposed plan of remedial action and final feasibility study for operable unit  have also been issued a public hearing on the proposed plan of remedial action for the burton island historical ash disposal site indian river generating stations operable unit  de was held on feb   in millsboro for more information please click here nrgs feasibility study for indian river generating stations operable unit no   final for burton island historical ash disposal area and other related documents are available at the links below cover letter for final fs  ou final fs  ou  text  appendix a  sediment comparison appendix b  food web model appendix c  postremediation risks appendix d  fs cost est summary appendix e  alternative ranking table final fs  figures secretarys order  approval of final plan of remedial action oufinal plan