ually of nitrogen oxide and  tons of sulfur dioxide elimination of  tons annually of the greenhouse gas carbon dioxide reduction in annual fly ash production of between  and  tons and reduction of mercury emissions by five pounds annually proposal to install controls on indian river power station unit  on february   the delaware department of natural resources and environmental control announced that it will continue with plans to place controls on nrg energys indian river power station unit  the largest unit at the indian river power station the project will cost approximately  million and create up to  constructions jobs over two years  cancellation of proposed fifth unit power wholesaler nrg energy which owns over  mw of powergenerating plants nationally planned to add a  mw igcc unit to its fourunit  mw total coalfired indian river power station the power would have been sold to retailer delmarva power in may  the delaware public service commission and three other state agencies ordered delmarva to negotiate with bluewater wind for a power purchase agreement for an offshore wind project that order foreclosed the indian river igcc project green delaware and citizens for clean power had opposed the expansion of indian river articles and resources sources ↑ form eia data  schedule  generator data us eia  ↑ the toll from coal an updated assessment of death and disease from americas dirtiest energy source clean air task force september  ↑ technical support document for the powerplant impact estimator software tool prepared for the clean air task force by abt associates july  ↑ nrg energy inc  k    business ↑ regulation  concent order sept   ↑ appendix for regulatory impact analysis for epa’s proposed rcra regulation of coal combustion residues generated by the electric utility industry ↑ eia  and schedule  of eia eia  schedules   ↑ nrg energy inc k february   ↑ phase ii coal ash landfill design narrative golder associates inc april  ↑ appendix for regulatory impact a